## AI daily planner

### Architecture

Frontend -> Angular (vercel)
Backend-> Node/NestJS (Render)
Database -> Supabase (Postgres + Auth)
AI -> OpenAI API
Memory -> DB (phase 1), vector (phase 2)

### Feature Design

1. Task Management
   Title, description, deadline, priority(Low/medium/high), estimated time(optional), status(pending/done)
2. AI "plan my day" feature
   input: today's task and user working hours
   output: sort by urgenry, allocate time slot, avoid overlaps, consider deadlines
3. Simple AI chat
   Input: can i finish everything today?
   Output: smart reasoning
4. Daily Schedule View
   Calender style, shows time slot and task
5. Authentication
   login/signup, user specific task

### AI flow

when user clicks "Plan my day"
Backend logic:

1. fetch user task
2. Filter for today
3. Structure Data
4. Send prompt to OpenAI
5. Parse AI Output
6. Store generate Schedule
7. Return to UI

### Prompt design

"""
You are an intelligent daily planning assistant.

Given a list of tasks, each with priority, deadline and estimated duration, create a realistic schdule for today.

Constraints:
-Work between 9:00 and 18:00
-Add short breaks if schedule is heavy
-Prioritize urgent and high-priority tasks
-avoid overlapping tasks

Return output in JSON format:
[
{ "task": "....", "start":"HH:MM", "end":"HH:MM" }
]

Tasks: {{tasks}} """

### Database Schema

Users handled by supabase Auth

Tasks table:

1. tasks
2. id
3. user-id
4. Title
5. description
6. priority
7. deadline
8. estimated time
9. status
   10 created_at

Schedule table:

1. schdule
2. id
3. user_id
4. Date
5. schdule_json
6. created_at

### Front end design

Pages:

1. dashboard -> task list, plan my day button
2. Schedule View -> timeline/cards View
3. AI chat panel -> simple input box, response area

Components:
TaskFrom
TaskList
Schedule
Chat

### Backend API design

Task APIs

1. get /task
2. post /tasks
3. put /tasks:id
4. delete /tasks/:id

AI planner API
Post ai/plan

Chat API
post ai/chat

---

Lets get into work
Initial setup:

1. create AI daily planner backend folder
2. generate json file: npm init -y
3. install express, cors, dotend, axios: npm i express cors dotenv axios
4. install nodemon: npm i --save-dev nodemon
5. Create folder Structure

---

1. configure env file
2. configure supabase DB
   npm install @supabase/supabase-js
3. configure taskController, taskRoutes and aiController, aiRoutes. Define index.js -- these files contain api methods, path and controls
4. configure openaiService -- this file contains the openRouter llm calls
5. Create middleware to set up authentication
6. To get the token, create a test user in supabase db
   username: test@gmail.com
   password: test123

- Go to postman, in send a POST method with the below details
  url: https://pcshyzlkjmvournzhegx.supabase.co/auth/v1/token?grant_type=password
  headers:
  apikey: eyJhbGciOiJI...
  Content-Type: application/json
  body:
  {
  "email": "test@gmail.com",
  "password": "test123"
  }
- in response, we get the access token, this is the JWT middleware token
